Program: Outlook
Title: Forced to Leave Home - The Domestic Abuse Victim
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbry5
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
People forced to leave their homes - the story of a victim of domestic abuse. Also, how climate change is affecting sking opportunities in the Bolivian Andes mountains. An interview with Iranian writer Shusha Guppy. The author of 'The Graduate', Charles Webb talks about facing eviction from his home in England. Finally, Dr Ngwache Francis, the blind director of the Savannah Botanical Garden, Cameroon. Show less